# MATLAB (chamberlain)

## File types

- **One function per file** when the file is named after that function (`cl_foo.m` → `function ... = cl_foo`).
- **Scripts** (`.m` without a leading `function`) must not contain `function` blocks. Use a separate `.m` file or a **function file with subfunctions** at the bottom.
- **Subfunctions** are allowed only inside a **function file**, after the main `function` body.

## Examples in headers

Every new function/script must start with a **runnable** example in the header comment (copy-paste into MATLAB):

```matlab
% Example:
%   report = cl_pulv_bodysignals_bacchus_build_db;
```

(chamberlain + helpers are on MATLAB path; no `addpath` in examples.)

No magic string dispatch (`switch example_name`) for “examples” — the body should be the real call with real paths.

## Layout

- Toolbox functions: `cl_*` at repo root; helpers in `helpers/`.
- Project code: `cl_<project>_*` in subfolders (e.g. `Pulv_bodysignals/`).

## Chamberlain workflow

| Task | Pattern |
|------|---------|
| New monkey/project | Copy `cl_example_create_penetration_db.m` → `Pulv_bodysignals/cl_<project>_<monkey>_build_db.m` |
| Build DB | Builder function + `cl_create_penetration_db(...)` + `MapGroup` subfunction; run via MCP → `*_penetration_db.m` |
| Visualization | Add `*_visualization_settings.m`; `cl_plot_electrode_localization(db, experiment_id)` |
| Plotting logic | `cl_plot_*` + `helpers/cl_*` — never duplicate in project files |
| Excel/MAT parsing | Only in `cl_create_penetration_db.m` |

Reference files: `cl_example_create_penetration_db.m` (template), `Pulv_bodysignals/cl_pulv_bodysignals_bacchus_build_db.m` (real project), `cl_create_penetration_db.m` (engine).

### Agent checklist (new `.m` files)

- [ ] Script OR function file — never mix
- [ ] Runnable `Example:` block with real paths
- [ ] `cl_` naming matches layout above
- [ ] If MCP available: `check_matlab_code` or run header example

### Prompt patterns (Agent + MCP)

- Syntax-check: `check_matlab_code` on changed `.m` files
- Run header example literally via `evaluate_matlab_code` or `run_matlab_file`
- Rebuild DB: run builder; confirm `ExpectedSiteCounts` in report
- Plot: `cl_plot_electrode_localization` with `*_visualization_settings.m` (Y: drive, BrainVoyager, shared MATLAB for figures)
- Debug: reproduce with `evaluate_matlab_code`, fix, re-run

## Before claiming code works

If MATLAB MCP tools are available (`evaluate_matlab_code`, `run_matlab_file`), use them. Otherwise say validation was not run in MATLAB. MCP setup: `.cursor/matlab_cursor_integration_readme.md`.
